If I read between the lines, you are saying that every "responsible" person for
a domain must have a mailbox somewhere outside of their realm so that if their
domain servers (both of them) crap out, you can still send mail to them?

I think it would be better for responsible parties of a domain list
their telephone number in the SOA rather than their primary mailbox.

--jsol

